The paper deals with the problem of multi-message private information retrieval (MPIR) using minimum storage regenerating (MSR) and minimum bandwidth regenerating (MBR) codes, which are classes of optimal regenerating codes providing efficient repair when a node in the system fails. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
